casebody.data:
Joseph C. ROSS v. UNITED STATES of America. No. 7962. Circuit Court of Appeals, Sixth Circuit. June 8, 1938. Zeno Fritz, of Pittsburgh, Pa., and Martin E. Blum and Henry A. Pollack, both of Cleveland Ohio, for appellant. E. B. Freed, U. S. Atty., of Cleveland, Ohio.

Before HICKS, SIMONS, and ALLEN, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

It is ordered that the appeal herein be and the same is dismissed, pursuant to stipulation of counsel.
